QuoteUnquote — Apple Pay domain association PLACEHOLDER (replace before going live)
============================================================================

WHAT THIS FILE IS
-----------------
Apple Pay on the web requires that every domain serving the Stripe Payment
Request Button be *verified*. Apple/Stripe verify a domain by fetching a
specific text file from this exact path, with no file extension:

    https://YOUR-DOMAIN/.well-known/apple-developer-merchantid-domain-association

server.js serves this ".well-known" directory as static text (with
dotfiles:'allow', because the folder name begins with a dot), so the verifier
can reach it in production.

HOW TO REPLACE IT
-----------------
1. In the Stripe Dashboard: Settings -> Payments -> Payment methods -> Apple Pay
   -> "Add a new domain", enter your production domain.
2. Stripe gives you the real association file (a long signed token).
   Alternatively call the Stripe API: POST /v1/apple_pay/domains.
3. Overwrite THIS file with that exact content — no comments, no extra
   whitespace, no file extension. Redeploy.
4. Verify it resolves as text/plain at the URL above, then re-run domain
   verification in the Dashboard.

Until you do this, the on-page Apple Pay button will simply not appear
(Google Pay and the card fallback continue to work). This human-readable
placeholder is intentionally NOT a valid association token.
